---
title: New York Strip Steaks in a Cherry Sauce With Gruyére Mashed Potatoes and Roasted Carrots
description: Treat your family to something special tonight: a steakhouse-style recipe that brings a bit of restaurant elegance right into your own kitchen. The centerpiece in this dish is four pieces of New York strip steak, a cut of beef known for its rich flavor. The meat is dressed up in a cherry balsamic sauce that has sophisticated and tart flavors for the adults and just enough sweetness to please the kids. On the side, tender roasted carrots and Parmesan Gruyére mashed potatoes (read: double extra cheesy) make this feast complete.
